 Boop, it's gone.

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:30.400
 Now we didn't put it in the trash can, we removed it.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:31.240
 It does it.

00:07:31.240 --> 00:07:33.360
 So you'll notice that db.zap is no longer

00:07:33.360 --> 00:07:35.040
 in my list of files.

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:39.800
 So be careful with the rm command,

00:07:39.800 --> 00:07:41.920
 but it's quite powerful and useful.

00:07:44.400 --> 00:07:45.640
 (clears throat)

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:50.640
 So this grep command, grep searches all the files.

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:54.760
 So if you look, I've got lots and lots and lots of files.

00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:59.160
 And so I'm going to say, grep minus r,

00:07:59.160 --> 00:08:03.680
 that means recursive, for a string autoscreate star

00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:04.600
 in all my files.

00:08:04.600 --> 00:08:06.880
 Now I got a lot of files here, so this is gonna be

